review_blob: Tap. Beige head with an orange color body. Smaller lacing with hoppy aromas. Malty medium bodied taste. Not phenomenal but not terrible either.

Both can and tap. Super solid amber ale! Good color, head, and lacing. Excellent creamy, malty taste with hoppy end. Great balance of powerful malty flavors and strong hops. Subtlety and balance is key with this really enjoyable american amber which I will definitely be drinking again during summer grilling or pre-game debacle!
Bomber. Almost completely black, beige head, nice lacing. Creamy, smooth and almost porter like. Great IBA to bad its only seasonal.
Really excellent IPA! Smooth orange and citrus flavor with a hoppy nose. Really great beer and highly recommended. One of my favorites so far for Michigan IPAs.
Bottle. Honey, wheat, and citrus aromas. Light and easy to drink wheat beer that left me pleasantly surprised. Definitely an easy drink to keep coming back to during a hot summer day.
12 oz. bottle. Clear pour light gold with a small white head. Medium sweet taste and light body. Not a huge fan but a satisfying lighter brew none the less.
16oz can. Pours pale yellow with a little bit of a citrusy bite. A cool refreshing beer that is not terrible but lacks a certain something to make it better than average.
Light and satisfying summer time brew.  Smooth finish with hints of wheat, barley and corn.  Very solid go to Wisconsin beer.
On tap at Steamworks.  Orange amber with short lasting white head.  Hoppy without being overbearing accompanied by a nice clean finish.
beer_name: Steamworks 3rd Eye Enlightened Pale Ale (Third Eye)

review_blob: Draft @ brewpub.  Flavor is lightly sweet and slightly bitter with an abrupt flavor.  While not a fan of many of Steamworks brand brews, Ale Diablo is a great drink with a little bit of kick.
Bottled.  Cloudy amber beige head.  Relatively fruity/earthy flavor with a touch of hops.  Slightly sweet with a dry finish.
Bottle.  Golden yellow, clear appearance with a white head.  Not extraordinary but drinkable run of the mill wheat beer.
Golden, pale and clear pour, with subtle aromas and taste.  Palate is pleasing and non invasive while remaining semi-reserved but highly drinkable.
Very dark brown pour with a tan head, nose is orange cream, with a cream and orange like palate.  A unique take on a creamsicle brew.
